ImgShark
========
Like a shark its, uh, good at resizing and storing images.

Install
-------
  
  gem install imgshark
  
Usage
-----

  require 'imgshark'
  
  # You can initialize it manually or use env variables.
  # The amazon env variables are named the same as the keys below.
  # The Redis env variable is REDISTOGO_URL so its heroku ready.
  imgshark = ImgShark.new(amazon_access_key_id: 'somekey', 
                          amazon_secret_access_key: 'shhhhh', 
                          redis_url: 'redis://whereisredis:someport/0')
  
  imgshark.exists?('http://example.com/example.png', 1, 1) # => false
  imgshark.upload('http://example.com/example.png', 1, 1, 'aws_bucket_name') # => true
  imgshark.exists?('http://example.com/example.png', 1, 1) # => true
